The Roman people were divided into thirty-five tribeS, strictly local and terri- torial‚ like wardS, but with the provision that the sons of citizens belonged to the tribe of their father, rather than to that in which they themselves resided. These tribes were made the basis of the comitia centuriata, as well as the comitia tributa.
